OL,3,CTwo accessible minibuses stolen in
OL,4,Cthree months from special school
OL,6,FDeputy headteacher Emma Love said:
OL,7,F"It's terrible. It's really
OL,8,Fdisappointing that someone from the
OL,9,Fcommunity, someone from the local area
OL,10,Fpossibly, has taken these minibuses
OL,11,Ffrom some of the most vulnerable young
OL,12,Fpeople that we've got here in
OL,13,FRotherham."JThe minibus were used to
OL,14,Ftransport students at the school,
OL,15,Fwhich looks after 76 children. It
OL,16,Fprovides access for large electric
OL,17,Fwheelchairs.JWithout a minibus,
OL,18,Fstudents can no longer be taken out
OL,19,Ffor activities including residentials,
OL,20,Fshopping and horseriding.
